From b501e6ac2eb42eba9da0bdc94b7ae3b0726e92fb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Torvaix Hardening Bot <torvaix-bot@local>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 17:56:51 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] feat(hardening): core infrastructure hardening - v0.2.0
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 1: Provider abstraction layer
- Unified LLMClient with adapters for Ollama, OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, Groq, OpenRouter
- Environment-based configuration
- Token usage tracking

Phase 2: Execution approval hardening
- Per-tool approvals with 5-minute expiry
- Workspace-scoped approval keys
- GC of expired approvals

Phase 3: Auth hardening
- SQLite user persistence with bcrypt hashing
- JWT session management (7-day expiry)
- Rate limiting middleware (60/min general, 30/min agent)
- requireAuth on all protected routes

Phase 4: Docker full stack
- docker-compose with torvaix + qdrant + ollama services
- Multi-stage Dockerfile with health checks

Phase 5: Hybrid router
- Regex fast-path for memory/knowledge/execution (zero latency)
- LLM fallback for ambiguous queries

Phase 6: MCP singleton lifecycle
- Persistent connection with lazy init
- Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff

Phase 7: Memory fallback chain
- Ollama embeddings → OpenAI embeddings → deterministic local

Phase 8: Agent trace improvements
- Routing/tool/LLM timing
- Token usage aggregation
- Approval pause tracking
- Error capture

Phase 9: Chat hook stabilization
- Replaced ts-expect-error with custom useTorvaixChat
- Proper streaming parser for AI SDK DataStream

Phase 10: Baseline tests
- Tests for providers, router, memory, trace, MCP client
- vitest configuration with path aliases
